description: One fateful day, Kiibo witnesses a hulking biker, Kuroda, rip a truck apart with his bare hands! Awed by Kuroda's super-human strength, Kiibo itches to take him on, and he soon gets his chance. But Kuroda hides a dark secret that could put Kiibo's life in mortal danger! Will fearless novice Kiibo be able to match--let alone defeat--mighty Kuroda in a no-holds-barred contest?!
name: Vol. 1

description: Kiibo's father crosses paths one day with Iron Kiba, the man he defeated in a bruising match years ago. Now a famous fight promoter, vengeful Kiba orders a pro-wrestler to take down Kiibo's father, but his cocky young son accepts the challenge instead! Even with his natural talent, can an amateur like Kiibo take on a pro who has never lost a street fight?!
name: Vol. 2

description: On a ship anchored miles from shore, Kiibo enters the ring to wage a do-or-die battle against the bloodthirsty fighter known as "The Beast." The Miyazawa family's sworn enemy, Iron Kiba, has staged the fight to crush their Nadashinkage school once and for all, and should Kiibo lose, the secret techniques will be made public. But when the bell rings, a spooked Kiibo freezes dead in his tracks!
name: Vol. 4

description: In his quest to master the Nadashinkage fighting style, Kiibo has honed his skills by defeating formidable opponents like pro wrestler Funada and Samon the Beast, an expert in freestyle fighting. But now Kiibo wants to test his strength in an unfamiliar sport--full-contact karate with boxing gloves. Only sanctioned moves are allowed in sports karate, however, so Kiibo will have to learn the rules fast!
name: Vol. 5

description: On a secluded beach swept by hurricane-force winds, Kiibo faces his greatest challenge yet: Nagahide Kaneda, the sadistic fighter who beat Kiibo in their last match. The same man almost killed Kiibo's friend Ashura, who secretly fought Kaneda to protect him. Now, Kiibo is more determined than ever to bring down Kaneda, but the fighter seems immune to every attack. Has Kiibo finally met a man he can't beat?
name: Vol. 6

description:
JOAN OF ARC

(1412-1431)

A patriotic young French maiden. After beginning to hear voices at the age of 13, Joan led the French army in the liberation of Orleans in the Hundred Years' War against Britain. But not long afterward, she was convicted of heresy by a religious tribunal and burned to death at the stake.

Chapter Seven to Twelve.
name: Vol. 2

description:
From the beloved creator of Inuyasha and Ranma 1/2, the wacky romantic comedy Maison Ikkoku, in a new edition in its original episodic order! Travel into Japan's nuttiest apartment house and meet its volatile inhabitants: Kyoko, the beautiful and mysterious new apartment manager; Yusaku, the exam-addled college student; Mrs. Ichinose, the drunken gossip; Kentaro, her bratty son; Akemi, the boozy bar hostess; and the mooching and peeping Mr. Yotsuya. Funny, touching, and a tad off-kilter, Maison Ikkoku is the great Rumiko Takahashi at her very best.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: What Are the Neighbors Doing?
  • Part Two: Mr. Soichiro
  • Part Three: Suit Yourself, Santa
  • Part Four: For Whom the Clock Tolls
  • Part Five: Hope Springs Eternal
  • Part Six: Will the Cherry Blossoms Bloom?
  • Part Seven: Spring Wasabi
  • Part Eight: Soichiro's Shadow
  • Part Nine: Alcohol Love Call
  • Part Ten: Don't Fence Me Out
name: Vol. 1

description:
Kyoko and Yusaku start dating--other people. She goes out with her handsome tennis instructor, Shun Mitaka, while he reluctantly dates Kozue, a former coworker. The two finally arrange to go on a date together, but a mix-up leads them to end up at different restaurants!

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: "Love" Means No Score, Godai!
  • Part Two: Dog Daze
  • Part Three: A Salty Dog
  • Part Four: Memorial Cooking
  • Part Five: One Entangled Evening
  • Part Six: 1-900-TROUBLE
  • Part Seven: With A Little Nonchalance
  • Part Eight: Campus Doll
  • Part Nine: Intensive Care
  • Part Ten: Shadows On the Heart
  • Part Eleven: Knit-Picking
name: Vol. 2

description:
Kyoko's meddling parents plot to get their daughter to give up her independence and move back home. Yusaku meets his (sort of) girlfriend's overzealous folks and then ends up on a never-ending visit to his own parents' house.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: Ring In the Nude
  • Part Two: "I'll Be Back"
  • Part Three: Stake It On the Rink!
  • Part Four: Kyoko Baby and Mr. Soichiro
  • Part Five: A Family Affair
  • Part Six: The Big Announcement
  • Part Seven: I'm Convinced
  • Part Eight: I'll Never give Up!
  • Part Nine: Mixed (Up) Doubles
  • Part Ten: Wait Three Years
  • Part Eleven: The Black Widow's Bite
name: Vol. 3

description:
How can Yusaku and Kyoko ever be alone when the motley crew at Maison Ikkoku are always inviting themselves to every get-together and social event? When the two finally have some one-on-one time, their housemates' gossip and meddling leads them to learn the hard way that home is where the heart is!

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: Catch of the Day
  • Part Two: Turn the Other Cheek
  • Part Three: Soichiro Turns Around
  • Part Four: A Bunch of Mugs
  • Part Five: The One That Got Away
  • Part Six: Memories of You
  • Part Seven: The Incident
  • Part Eight: A Small Space
  • Part Nine: Recipe For Misunderstanding
  • Part Ten: The Light In Room 5
  • Part Eleven: Down the Home Stretch
name: Vol. 4

description:
Yusaku's New Year's fortune comes true, but he quickly learns he should be careful what he wishes for. When Valentine's Day arrives, Yusaku receives flowers from Kozue and then soon after from Kyoko--each with their own meaning.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: Embraced By Illness
  • Part Two: The Man Who Reached For the Stars
  • Part Three: Careful What You Wish For
  • Part Four: The Kissing Scene
  • Part Five: No Peeking!
  • Part Six: Mixed Messages
  • Part Seven: The Better To Hear You With
  • Part Eight: Clothes Make the ???
  • Part Nine: Just A Little Card
  • Part Ten: Oh, Baby
name: Vol. 5

description:
Grandma Godai comes for an extended visit and manages to meddle in Yusaku's love life at every turn. Before she leaves, Grandma brokers a dream date for her wishy-washy grandson, but the night doesn't turn out exactly as she planned...

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: A Very Tight Game
  • Part Two: Shall We... Rest Awhile?
  • Part Three: Grandma Goes To Town
  • Part Four: Stop Following Me!
  • Part Five: Come On A My House
  • Part Six: Granny's Ol' Plum Wine
  • Part Seven: Playing Hickey
  • Part Eight: A Hot Wind
  • Part Nine: Well, Well, Well
  • Part Ten: Prune-Faced Cupid
  • The Lost Episode: Yusaku's Island
name: Vol. 6

description:
Yusaku ends up in the hospital and has two unexpected visitors. His cute cousin comes to nurse him and Kyoko's other suitor, Mitaka, ends up being his roommate. Yusaku's problems aren't over when he's discharged--he has to deal with Kyoko and his school absences.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: Farewell On Platform 18
  • Part Two: Mr. Ichinosa Gets Laid Off
  • Part Three: Run, Ichinose, Run
  • Part Four: Falling For You
  • Part Five: No Visitors, Please!
  • Part Six: Mission Impossible: The Party Cracker Case
  • Part Seven: Body of Love
  • Part Eight: Message In the Snow
  • Part Nine: Mending A Break
  • Part Ten: Just Do Your Best!
name: Vol. 7

description:
Yusaku's eavesdropping causes him to misunderstand Kyoko's words--again. This time, it's during Kyoko's visit to her former husband's graveside. A new wide-eyed tenant, Nozomu Nikaido, moves into room No. 2 and quickly causes trouble for the other Maison Ikkoku residents, especially Yusaku in his pursuit of Kyoko.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: In Hot Water
  • Part Two: Going Shopping In A Suit
  • Part Three: The Face In the Darkness
  • Part Four: A Grave Matter
  • Part Five: One Big Happy Family
  • Part Six: Attack and Counterattack
  • Part Seven: Can't We Be Friends?
  • Part Eight: Even If We're Caught In the Rain
  • Part Nine: Total Insensitivity
  • Part Ten: Nothing... Nothing At All!
  • Part Eleven: The Scramble Kid
name: Vol. 8

description: Yusaku finally gets serious about finding a job. Unfortunately, Kyoko is the only one who takes him seriously--a little too seriously--when he talks about his "future." For the immediate future, he gets a position waiting tables at a resort, and an eyeful when Kyoko loses her top in the pool. Once he finally lands a gig student-teaching at Kyoko's old high school, a googly-eyed student named Yagami moves into his life, and, sneakily, into Maison Ikkoku. Will she manage to get between Yusaku and Kyoko?
name: Vol. 9

description: The not-so-simple life of the tenants of Maison Ikkoku is sent reeling (yet again) after the latest Godai-related scandal hits the fan...a hostage situation! But there's a twist--the hostage is Ibuki Yagami, a coquettish coed smitten by Yusaku's bumbling charms, and she refuses to vacate the premises until her outlandish demands are met. Can Godai successfully broker her freedom...as well as his own?! Plus, Coach Mitaka's life (both literally and figuratively) goes to the dogs.
name: Vol. 10

description: Now they've gone and done it! After chancing upon the lovely Kyoko and the rakish Coach Mitaka in an oh-so-compromising situation, bumbling gadabout Godai's little world is sent twirling off its axis...again! Attempting to quell the memory of her indiscrete dalliance (and hoping to get some rest and relaxation), Kyoko arranges to take a much-needed vacation. Hot on her trail, though, is Godai, hoping for a reconciliation rendezvous. Will these accidental tourists be reunited on a weekend getaway, or remain strangers on a train?
name: Vol. 11

description: Finding himself in dire straights (yet again), Godai is forced to scramble for a job after being summarily laid off from his teaching gig. Thanks to a recommendation from a friend, he embarks on a brilliant new career in "public relations"...at a strip club. In addition to the ignominy of the job itself, Godai quickly finds himself in the role of de facto daddy when one of the hostesses absconds without her children. One little boy, one little girl, and a household of drunks...the fates are certainly testing (and flagrantly taunting) our poor Godai.
name: Vol. 13

description: Coach Mitaka is dashing, athletic, financially set, and extraordinarily popular with the ladies, but there's one little aspect of his personality that has curtailed his success with the lovely Kyoko from day one--his crippling, petrifying, and all-around embarrassing fear of dogs (Kyoko's dog Soichiro in particular). Mitaka has gone into seclusion to cure himself of his phobia, promising that he will return as a new man...But will he emerge from his canine-chrysalis in time to win Kyoko's heart, or will his lot be forever thrown in with the shy, patrician, and multiple dog-loving heiress Asuna?
name: Vol. 12
Vol. 14

description:
"The woman I love burns with jealousy, leaps to conclusions, cries, and turns to ice, but when she laughs, the world is mine." Such are Yusaku Godai's feelings for Kyoko Otonashi, the beautiful manager of Maison Ikkoku--the ramshackle boarding house he has lived in since his days as a struggling student. Over the years, his love for Kyoko has grown, and nothing fate threw in his way could keep him from pursuing Kyoko's affections. Will she finally reciprocate Godai's heartfelt sentiments, or has he simply wasted his life pining for a woman beyond his reach? All endings lead to new beginnings in this unforgettable conclusion to Rumiko Takahashi's Maison Ikkoku, one of the most beloved of all manga series.

Chapter Titles

  • Part One: The Truth
  • Part Two: Sacred Vows
  • Part Three: Love Call
  • Part Four: Wait For Me Tonight
  • Part Five: Sympathy
  • Part Six: ...If It Ever Happens
  • Part Seven: Promises
  • Part Eight: Heirlooms
  • Part Nine: Beneath the Cherry Tree
  • Part Ten: P. S. Ikkoki
name: Vol. 15

description:
A dream recaptured. A life on a new track. The absurdity of death.

Laughter in the face of reality.

With this series of intersecting vignettes, Inio Asano explores the ways in which modern life can be ridiculous and sublime, terrible and precious, wasted and celebrated.
name: Vol. 1

description: The cruelty of childhood. The delusion of adulthood. The endurance of death. _Laugh in the face of reality. __With this series of intersecting vignettes, Inio Asano explores the ways in which modern life can be ridiculous and sublime, terrible and precious, wasted and celebrated.
name: Vol. 2

description:
The Five Nightmares builds to its penultimate chapter. Stane and his army make their assault against Stark -- the man and the conglomerate -- and Tony Stark shows even an old dog can pick up a trick or two when his back's against the wall. Iron Man and Iron Man 2.0 finally come face-to-face and head-to-head!

Also, it's Bucky versus Batroc and a mysterious foreign agent from his past as the Winter Soldier, as he fights to keep a secret super-weapon from falling into enemy hands! But the shocking ending of this tale brings a new twist to the mission... and sends our New Captain America in search of whatever is left of his old comrades, the Invaders!

Plus, Thor battles the all-powerful Bor in a desperate fight to save New York! As the conflict rages and the city trembles, the thunder god is joined by the Avengers, but not as you know them! These are the Dark Avengers!

Includes material reprinted from Invincible Iron Man #5, Captain America #45 and Thor #600!

description: The Hokuto Cup, a new tournament for young players from Japan, China and Korea, is looming, and Hikaru's rival Akira has already secured one of the coveted three places on Japan's team. While Hikaru battles his way to one of the two remaining spots, Akira's father baffles the go world with his unexpected retirement!
name: Great Expectations

description: Sati sends Yoh to train in the strangest place yet: the underworld. But when he arrives he is attacked by Yohken Asakura, an ancestor who defeated Hao in the previous Shaman Fight! How can Yoh defend himself against such a powerful shaman when he doesn't even have the Futsu-no-Mitama Sword with him?
name: Exotica

description:
The Dark Knight Returns is a possible future for Batman. Bruce Wayne has retired from being the Dark Knight of Gotham however with the rise of the Mutant Gang he decides to return becomes the protector of the night once more. After Batman's re-emergence old rivals surface and Bruce battles Two-Face and foils his plan to bomb Gotham's Two Towers.

Bruce's actions go on to inspire Carrie Kelly to become the next Robin and joins Batman in his fight to regain control of Gotham. After the Mutant Leader's defeat the United States is conflicted over the actions of Batman once more and Superman is asked by the President to talk him down. Many of the previous mutants choose to become the Sons of the Batman, while others continue their pursuits of crime under different mantels.

The Joker is released and goes on a wave of terror upon which the Dynamic Duo face him, ending with the death of the Joker. During these events the US and Russia via for control of Corto Maltese and the US manages a swift victory with the aid of Superman. Upon defeat the Russian's choose to fire a nuclear weapon which is diverted by Superman but still releases an EMP knocking out all of the power in Gotham City. Chaos ensues and Batman and the citizens of Gotham, including the Sons of the Batman, fight to restore order.

Superman is then tasked with taking down Batman and a dual between the two most prominent DC heroes takes place. Bruce ends up chemically inducing a heart attack to fake his own death. Batman's identity is as a result released to the general public and when he returns we are left with the prospect of Batman training the Sons of the Batman and Carrie Kelly to replace him.

Notes:

  • Trade Paperback release date: 14 October 1986.

description:
Reprints:

  • Captain America #12.
  • Iron Man #36.
  • Thor #32.

Reprints "The Winter Soldier(Part Five)" from Captain America #13, "TheFrankenstein Syndrome(Part One)" from Iron Man Annual [volume 3] #46, and "The Million Dollar Debut of Thor Girl!" from Thor [volume 2]#32.
Reprints "The Winter Soldier(conclusion)" from Captain America #14, "TheFrankenstein Syndrome(Part Two)" from Iron Man Annual [volume 3] #47, and "The Man of Tomorrow!" from Thor [volume 2]#34.
Reprints "Red is the Darkest Colour" from Captain America #15, "TheFrankenstein Syndrome(Part Three)" from Iron Man Annual [volume 3] #48, and "Across All Worlds (Part One)" from Thor [volume 2]#35.
Reprints "Captain America: House of M" from Captain America #10, "Father's Day" from Iron Man: House of M #1, and "Across All Worlds (Part Two)" from Thor [volume 2] #35.

100 page special!

It's all-out World War II action as Cap, Bucky and Nick Fury's Howling Commandos embark on a dangerous mission behind enemy lines in an attempt to thwart the Red Skull!

By Ed Brubaker, Javier Pulido and Marcos Martin.

Also: an incredible new Iron Man saga begins, as Shellhead seeks to discover the secret of Extremis!

By Warren Ellis and Adi Granov.

Plus: we present he origin of Iron Man by Stan Lee and Don Heck, and we take a look at the new Iron Man movie in a special feature.

Also: Thor versus the Destroyer! 'Nuff Said!

By Dan Jurgens and Stuart Immonen.

Captain America, Bucky and Nick Fury learn that time is running out - the Red Skull's villainous scheme is almost complete!

By Ed Brubaker, Javier Pulido, Maros Martin and Mike Perkins.

Plus: Iron Man is determined to find out who stole Extremis! Meanwhile, Mallen, the man responsible makes his move!

By Warren Ellis and Adi Gravnov.

Also: Surtur and his demoniac legions attack - and somebody dies!

By Dan Jurgens and Stuart Immonen.

Iron Man is guilty of murder, but how is Tony Stark going to prove he's innocent?

By Daniel Way, Charles Knauf and Pat Zircher.

Also: Captain America reveals some incredible secrets to Corporal Newman!

By David Morrell and Mitch Breitweiser.

Plus: while Thor rules in Asgard, Tarene struggles to fill in for the Thunder God on Earth!

By Dan Jurgens and Tom Raney

A Civil War chapter!

While the war rages, the Winter Soldier and the Young Avengers face hideous hordes of Hydra!

By Ed Brubaker and Lee Weeks.

Also: can Captain America and Iron man stop the war before and more blood is spilt?!

By Christos N Gage and Jeremy Haun.

Plus: Thor brings Asgard to New York! Guest-starring Spider-Man!

By Dan Jurgens and Tom Raney.

Time is running out for humanity. Tony Stark, discredited, humiliated and stripped of his command, struggles to uncover a diabolical plot that could spell the end of mankind. Betrayed by his peers, isolated by his obsessions, Stark finds that his only allies are the demons of his past and, hamstrung by obsolete technology, Iron Man is confronted by his archenemy, The Mandarin.

Also, the new Captain America fights the Red Skull's minions with Black Widow at his side and chaos erupting all around them! Meanwhile, Sharon Carter, still under the control of Dr. Faustus, makes a horrifying discovery about the next stage of the Skull's plans!

Plus, the Secret Invasion hits Asgard and Broxton, Oklahoma, isn't spared! As the Skrulls arrive and begin their massive assault on the Norse gods, Dr. Donald Blake has his hands full in a middle-school basement delivering a baby. Can Balder the Brave and Beta Ray Bill marshal Asgard's forces long enough, and fight back hard enough, to hold the line until the God of Thunder joins them? And can anybody survive the Skrull's secret weapon?

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #36, Iron Man #25 and Secret Invasion: Thor #2!

With a new Cap now established, things go from bad to worse as the Red Skull makes an unexpected move for the very soul of America!

Also, all paths have led to this: the inevitable showdown between Iron Man and the Mandarin!

As the man behind the mask, Tony Starks life has hit rock bottom. His plans for the super hero Initiative have hit a tragic snag. His former flame, believed dead, is being manipulated by one of his deadliest enemies. Even to his strongest allies, Stark appears to be descending into a mental breakdown while everything around him swirls out of control. Now, with the lives of millions hanging in the balance, Iron Man must fight his way out of the darkness and prevent the Mandarin from releasing a plague that would change humanity as we know it!

Plus, a Secret Invasion chapter! Thor and Beta Ray Bill stand against a god-killing Skrull armada, hell-bent on seeing Asgard rent asunder, and burning Broxton, Oklahoma, down to the ground. With innocent lives to save, two cities to defend, an alien army to stop, and a marauding super-Skrull scientifically engineered to destroy themcan Bill and Thor possibly survive?

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #37, Iron Man #26 and Secret Invasion: Thor #3!

Bucky Barnes never wanted to be Captain America, but he's doing his best to carry on the legacy of Steve Rogers, in his own way, while trying to save Sharon Carter from the Red Skull and his minions. But maybe he's not the only one running around in a Captain America outfit!

Also, the Mandarin will go to any length to release the Extremis virus into the populace, in order to commit global genocide. Meanwhile, Iron Man and his fellow S.H.I.E.L.D. leaders are confined under house arrest, helpless to prevent humankinds destruction.

Plus, Thor enters the recuperating Odinsleep. However, while in this coma-like state his spirit wanders the world between life and death, where he must face dark truths!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #38, Iron Man #27 and Thor #7!

It's Cap versus Cap for the future of the American Dream as the Red Skull looks on in laughter! And Bucky learns the true identity of the man behind the other mask!

Plus, an incredible new Iron Man adventure begins! Tony Stark Iron Man, billionaire industrialist and director of S.H.I.E.L.D. faces the most overwhelming challenge of his life. Ezekiel Stane, the son of Tonys late business rival and archenemy Obadiah, has set his sights, his genius and his considerable fortune on the task of destroying Tony Stark and Iron Man. Whats worse, hes got Iron Man tech, and hes every bit Iron Mans equal and oppositeexcept younger, faster, smarterand immeasurably evil!

Also, Asgard and its people have been fully restoredand now Thor can turn his attention beyond the shining city! However, while the Thunder Gods attention is elsewhere his evil half-brother Loki begins to sow the seeds of discord in the heart of Asgard!

Includes material reprinted from Captain America #40, Invincible Iron Man #1 and Thor #9!

Prince Hali and the White Stallion part 2

description: The secrets of the Scarlett Redeemer begin to unfold as Scarlett arrives in a Houston strangely devoid of life. But she finds plenty of action beneath the streets, as Montero battles Sligoth, the unholy lurker below.
name: Blood of the City: Chapter One

description: The vampire forces and the Nomads converge on Houston for their final showdown! Scarlett and her allies battle the flame-wielding mutant vampire Afterburn, while the unspeakable Sligoth is summoned to rain death on the city.
name: Blood of the City: Chapter Two

description: Centuries after an army of Nomads battled a Sligoth and, at great cost in lives, defeated the beast, Scarlett and her allies must now stop an even more powerful Sligoth from devouring Houston. But while they battle for their lives...Bloodtide draws near!
name: Blood of the City: Chapter Three

description: Scarlett and her allies have defeated the Sligoth, but now they must face his master, the Gearsman, and learn the startling truth of his origin. Plus, the return of the Blood Wing.
name: Blood of the City: Chapter Four
